### System:
You are an AI assistant who gives quality response to whatever humans ask of you.

### Human:
what does this command do: ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com

### Assistant:

The command creates a secure shell (SSH) connection to the Amazon EC2 instance with the IP address "ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com" using the private key file "~/UserKey.pem". It also creates a local SOCKS proxy on port 25900 that tunnels traffic to port 5900 on the remote host. This allows you to access the remote host as if it were running locally on your machine, but with added security and encryption provided by SSH.
